To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, I need to divide the Gross Profit by the Total Revenue, then express it as a percentage.

From the income statement:
- Gross Profit = $8,372,608.70
- Total Revenue = $28,572,608.70

Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = ($8,372,608.70 / $28,572,608.70) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 0.2930 × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 29.30%
